# Runaway fixture for the #651 runaway-guard self-test. NOT run by the normal
# suite: the leading underscore keeps it out of test_*.eigs discovery, and
# run_all_tests.sh drives it ONLY through the dedicated self-test block.
#
# This program never terminates on ANY hardware. EigenScript hard-caps a single
# loop at 100,000,000 iterations (vm.c eigs_loop_cap_step), so a lone
# `loop while 1 == 1` would force-exit after the cap (a few seconds) and be a
# "runaway" only relative to a sub-cap timeout budget. Nesting defeats that: the
# inner loop force-exits at the cap, the outer loop immediately re-enters it,
# and total runtime is unbounded -- so the guard's timeout MUST fire, whatever
# the box speed.
i is 0
loop while 1 == 1:
    loop while 1 == 1:
        i is i + 1
